  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_cardiopulmonary_exercise_test">Cardiopulmonary Exercise Test</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_clinical_investigation">Clinical Investigation</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_cardiopulmonary_exercise_test">Cardiopulmonary Exercise Test</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_cardiopulmonary_exercise_test">CPET</xref>
) is a non-invasive method used to assess the performance of the heart and lungs at rest and during exercise.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_cardiopulmonary_exercise_test">Cardiopulmonary Exercise Test</xref>
 is for:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Incremental Shuttle Walk Test (ISWT) or</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Oxygen Consumption (VO2).</p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>

